<p>How can I limit the number of pages in pagination? Currently there are 100+ pages in pagination. This is the code example which I use</p>  <pre><code>if (isset($_GET["page"])) { $page = $_GET["page"]; } else { $page=1; }; $start_from = ($page-1) * 20; $result = $pdo-&gt;prepare("SELECT * FROM table LIMIT $start_from, 20"); $result-&gt;execute();  for($i=0; $row = $result-&gt;fetch(); $i++) {     // results } $result = $pdo-&gt;prepare("SELECT COUNT(id) FROM table");         $result-&gt;execute();         $row = $result-&gt;fetch();         $total_records = $row[0];         $total_pages = ceil($total_records / 20);          for ($i=1; $i&lt;=$total_pages; $i++) {             echo "&lt;a href='?page=".$i."'";             if($page==$i)             {                 echo "class=active";             }                 echo "&gt;";                 echo "".$i."&lt;/a&gt; "; }; </code></pre>  <p>Update: What I want is to have lets say 2 pages before and after current page. So for example:</p>  <p><strong>1</strong> 2 3 >></p>  <p>&lt;&lt; 9 10 <strong>11</strong> 12 13 >></p>